MPs continue to debate President Cyril Ramaphosa's State of the Nation Address * This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. CAPE TOWN - The National Assembly and the National Council of Provinces are holding another sittings on Wednesday to debate the State of the Nation Address. Tough questions regarding the AstraZeneca vaccine being returned to India, the ailing economy and the crisis at Eskom are likely to be raised. READ: #SONA2021 focuses on COVID-19, economy and corruption The debate and the president's reply will take the form of hybrid sittings. In line with COVID-19 regulations, there are a limited number of MPs and media present in the chamber.